thread.title_full: Australian stock market looks set to open higher

author: AAP
title: Australian stock market looks
text:
The Australian share market looks set to open higher. Picture: AP/Richard Drew
AAP news.com.au Share Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share on Google+ Share on Reddit Email a friend THE Australian share market looks set to open solidly higher after US and European shares rose despite disappointing US jobs data, seen as pushing back the timing of a US interest rate rise.
At 0645 AEDT on Monday, the December 67 points at 5,098.
Locally, in economic news on Monday, the ANZ job advertisements series, the TD Securities-Melbourne Institute’s inflation gauge and the Australian Industry Group’s Australian Performance of Services Index (PSI), all for September, are due out.
In equities news, Djerriwarrh Investments has its annual general meeting.
 Friday fell one per cent in the final session of a tumultuous week, leaving it at levels close to where it was seven days previously.
The benchmark S & P/ASX200 index was down 60.1 points, or 1.18 per cent, at 5,052 was down 54.9 points, or 1.07 per cent, at 5,089.2
